JOHANNESBURG No ANC MPs will vote with opposition parties and impeach President Jacob Zuma in Parliament, said ANC secretary general Gwede Mantashe. That would be uncharacteristic of the ANC really. We have a party-political system there will be no such a thing as motion of no-confidence in the president. There will be no ANC member who will vote for a motion from the opposition no self-respecting army would allow to be commanded by the enemy, Mantashe said.READ: Mantashe says Zuma was correct to fire GordhanThis as opposition parties, ANC veterans and civic organisations, as well as tripartite alliance partners Cosatu and SACP called for Zuma to resign.Opposition party leaders said they would do everything to have Zuma removed from office, including mass mobilisation and protests, court action and a motion of no-confidence tabled by the DA in Parliament.The opposition parties said ANC MPs should introspect and choose Zuma and the Guptas or the people .READ: 'We will not stop until he steps down' - Save SA on ZumaLast week, EFF leader Julius Malema said that his party would support the motion of no-confidence against Zuma, and that the EFF had the support of some of the ANC top leaders.He added that work was under way to woo ANC MPs who would be approached individually, in a collaborative effort along with the opposition parties to sway the vote against Zuma. African News Agency